Class Vector

  • java.lang.Object
    • Vector

  • public class Vector
extends java.lang.Object
    The Vector class defines the central data structure of the project, a vector of 'd' dimensions, which contains a String key (name, word) and an array of doubles which are the doubles in the specified dimensions
    Since:
    26-04-2019
    Author:
    Luke Byrne, Lilian Morgan, Heather Lloyd

              double[] vectors,
              int dimensions)
        Standard constructor with parametres for all three instance variables described above
        Parameters:
        name - = the word from the vector and its key
        vectors - = the list of vectors for this word
        dimensions - = the amount of dimensions this word has, or in other words the amount of vectors it has
